# Witch Hunter Orders
Order Of The Ghostslayer			KEY:Witch Hunter ~ Order Of The Ghostslayer			CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Order.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:The Order of the Ghostslayer is the oldest and most 'pure' of the orders, having roots in divine practices and created specifically to rid the realms of the scourge of undeath. Ghostslayers seek out and study the moment of death, obsessing over the mystery of the transition. Some will sit with the terminally diseased to closely witness their passing, while others go so far as to deliberately have a near-death experience, allowing them to tune their senses to the ethereal realms beyond.	ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Ghostslayer ~ Cleansing Rite|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,3			ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Ghostslayer ~ Stubborn Vitality|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,7	ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Ghostslayer ~ Hallowed Rune|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,10			ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Ghostslayer ~ Gravesight|Order Of The Ghostslayer ~ Supernal Riposte|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,15			ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Ghostslayer ~ Voracious Strike|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,18		
Order Of The Profane Soul			KEY:Witch Hunter ~ Order Of The Profane Soul			CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Order.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Long ago, a demonic evil rose to power that had slaughtered with such cruelty that it broke the minds of many a witch hunter who bore witness. A few brave, and possibly mad hunters saw that such depravity cou ld only be fought if you understood it, embraced it. and used it against itself. These few reached out to and made pacts with lesser evils, entities that hungered for a covenant with mortals, feeding on their hubris. Using their new-found magical prowess, they felled the terrible demon at a great personal cost. Understanding the potential power, and burden, of their dark dealing and acquired warlock spellcraft, they began a new sect of witch hunters. Thus began the Order of the Profane Soul.	ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Pact Magic|Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Cantrips|Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Spell Slots|Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Spells Known Of 1st Level And Higher|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,3		ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Lethal Focus|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,3						ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Mystic Frenzy|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,7						ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Diabolic Channel|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,10					ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Arcane Impulse|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,15						ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Insidious Boon|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,18					
Order Of The Mutant				KEY:Witch Hunter ~ Order Of The Mutant				CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Order.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:The process of consuming the Hunter's Bane is a painful, scarring, and often fatal experience. Those that survive find themselves irrevocably changed, enhanced. Some found this experience exalting, embracing the ability to alter one's own body and abilities through alchemy. Over generations of experimentation, a splinter order of witch hunters began to emerge, one that focused on brewing toxic elixirs to modify their capabilities in battle, and over time become something beyond human. They called themselves the Order of the Mutant.	ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Mutant ~ Formulas|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,3	ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Mutant ~ Mutagen Craft|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,3	ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Mutant ~ Advanced Mutagen Craft|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,7	ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Mutant ~ Robust Physiology|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,10	ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Mutant ~ Strange Metabolism|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,15	ABILITY:Witch Hunter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Order Of The Mutant ~ Exalted Fortitude|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,18

# Order Of The Ghostslayer
Cleansing Rite					KEY:Order Of The Ghostslayer ~ Cleansing Rite					CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Ghostslayer.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:When you join this order at 3rd level, you learn to alter your Blood Rite to channel the wrath of the Light, smiting the enemies of life itself. Whenever you deal elemental damage with your Blood Rite die, you also deal additional radiant damage equal to your Wisdom modifier.
Stubborn Vitality					KEY:Order Of The Ghostslayer ~ Stubborn Vitality				CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Ghostslayer.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 7th level, your physical body has become resistant to the life-draining cu rses or the most twisted of monsters. Whenever you are subject to Ability damage or a reduction in your Maximum hit points by an enemy attack or enemy spell, you halve the amount suffered (rounded up).
Hallowed Rune					KEY:Order Of The Ghostslayer ~ Hallowed Rune					CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Ghostslayer.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Beginning at 10th level, your binding magics transcend the prime material plane, grasping spirits and entities between physical states. Your Rune of Binding ability ignores immunity to the restrained condition.
Gravesight						KEY:Order Of The Ghostslayer ~ Gravesight						CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Ghostslayer.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:When you become 15th level, your vision has been so tuned to the ethereal curtain between worlds that even the unseeable cannot escape your view. You can see in normal and magical darkness, as well as invisible creatures and objects, up to 60 ft. Furthermore, you can see into the Ethereal Plane up to 60 ft.
Supernal Riposte					KEY:Order Of The Ghostslayer ~ Supernal Riposte					CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Ghostslayer.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 15th level, you develop risky methods to goad your enemies into a vulnerable position. When a creature makes an attack of opportunity against you and misses, you can immediately use your reaction to make one melee attack against that creature. The attack interrupts your movement, occuring right after their attack and before they leave your reach.
Voracious Strike					KEY:Order Of The Ghostslayer ~ Voracious Strike					CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Ghostslayer.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Upon reaching 18th level, you've learned the secret to draining the lifeforce of your quarry through a vicious attack. Before attacking, you can declare your next strike to be a Voracious Strike. If the blow hits your foe, you regain hit points equal to half of the total damage dealt by that attack. If the attack misses, your Voracious Strike is still expended. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (a minimum of once). You regain any expe nded uses when you finish a long rest.

# Order Of The Profane Soul
Pact Magic						KEY:Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Pact Magic									CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Profane Soul.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:When you reach 3rd level, you can augment your combat techniques with the ability to cast Warlock spells. See chapter 10 (phb) for the general rules of spellcasting and chapter 11 (phb) for the Warlock spell list.
Cantrips						KEY:Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Cantrips										CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Profane Soul.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:You learn two cantrips of your choice from the warlock spell list. You learn an additional warlock cantrip of your choice at 10th level.	DEFINE:POOL_Warlock_Cantrip|0	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Warlock_Cantrip|2+(WitchHunterLVL>=10)
Spell Slots						KEY:Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Spell Slots									CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Profane Soul.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:The Profane Soul Spellcasting table shows how many spell slots you have. The table also shows what the level of those slots is; all of your spell slots are the same level. To cast one of your warlock spells of 1st level or higher, you must expend a spell slot. You regain all expended spell slots when you finish a short or long rest. For example, when you are 8th level, you have two 2nd-level spell slots. To cast the 1st-level spell thunderwave, you must spend one of those slots, and you cast it as a 2nd-level spell.	BONUS:SPELLCAST|Class=Witch Hunter;Level=1|WitchHunterCastSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,3	BONUS:SPELLCAST|Class=Witch Hunter;Level=2|WitchHunterCastSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,7	BONUS:SPELLCAST|Class=Witch Hunter;Level=3|WitchHunterCastSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,11	BONUS:SPELLCAST|Class=Witch Hunter;Level=4|WitchHunterCastSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,18	BONUS:SPELLCAST|Class=Witch Hunter;Level=1|-WitchHunterCastSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,7	BONUS:SPELLCAST|Class=Witch Hunter;Level=2|-WitchHunterCastSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,11	BONUS:SPELLCAST|Class=Witch Hunter;Level=3|-WitchHunterCastSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,18	DEFINE:WitchHunterCastSlotCount|0	BONUS:VAR|WitchHunterCastSlotCount|1+(WitchHunter>=8)+(WitchHunter>=17)
Spells Known Of 1st Level And Higher	KEY:Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Spells Known Of 1st Level And Higher					CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Profane Soul.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 3rd level, you know two 1st-level spells of your choice from the warlock spell list. The Spells Known column of the Profane Soul table shows when you learn more warlock spells of your choice of 1st level and higher. A spell you choose must be of a level no higher than what's shown in the table's Slot Level column for your level. When you reach 11th level, for example, you learn a new warlock spell, which can be 1st, 2nd, or 3rd level. Additionally, when you gain a level in this class and Order, you can choose one of the warlock spells you know and replace is with another spell from the warlock spell list, which also must be of a level for which you have spell slots. Spellcasting Ability.  Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for your warlock spells, so you use your Wisdom whenever a spell refers to your spellcasting ability. In addition, you use your Wisdom modifier when setting the saving throw DC for a warlock spell you cast and when making an attack roll with one. Spell save DC = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier Spell attack modifier = your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier	BONUS:SPELLKNOWN|Class=Witch Hunter;Level=1|WitchHunterKnownSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,3	BONUS:SPELLKNOWN|Class=Witch Hunter;Level=2|WitchHunterKnownSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,8	BONUS:SPELLKNOWN|Class=Witch Hunter;Level=3|WitchHunterKnownSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,11	BONUS:SPELLKNOWN|Class=Witch Hunter;Level=4|WitchHunterKnownSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,18	BONUS:SPELLKNOWN|Class=Witch Hunter;Level=1|-WitchHunterKnownSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,8	BONUS:SPELLKNOWN|Class=Witch Hunter;Level=2|-WitchHunterKnownSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,11	BONUS:SPELLKNOWN|Class=Witch Hunter;Level=3|-WitchHunterKnownSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,18	DEFINE:WitchHunterKnownSlotCount|0	BONUS:VAR|WitchHunterKnownSlotCount|2+(WitchHunter>=5)+(WitchHunter>=7)+(WitchHunter>=9)+(WitchHunter>=11)+(WitchHunter>=13)+(WitchHunter>=15)+(WitchHunter>=17)+(WitchHunter>=18)+(WitchHunter>=20)
Lethal Focus					KEY:Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Lethal Focus									CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Profane Soul.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 3rd level, your weapon becomes a core to your pact with your chosen dark patron. You can use your weapon as a spellcasting focus (found in chapter 5, phb) for your warlock spells.
Mystic Frenzy					KEY:Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Mystic Frenzy									CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Profane Soul.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Beginning at 7th level, when you use your action to cast a cantrip, you can make one weapon attack as a bonus action.
Diabolic Channel					KEY:Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Diabolic Channel								CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Profane Soul.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 10th level, you can temporarily infuse your weapon with the seed of a powerful spell. As an action, you can imbue your weapon or a piece of ammunition with one spell you can cast, then make a single attack with that weapon. If that attack hits. the target takes weapon damage, and is subject to the effects of the spell. The spell must have a casting time of 1 action and must target only that creature. If the attack misses, the spell misses. and you s till expend a use of this feature. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (a minimum of one). You regain any expended uses when you finish a long rest.
Arcane Impulse					KEY:Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Arcane Impulse									CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Profane Soul.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Upon reaching 15th level, you learn to utilize a foe's error as an opportunity to retaliate with vicious magic. If an enemy attack misses you, you can use your reaction to immediately cast a spell at that creature. The spell must have a casting time of 1 action and must target only that creature. Once you use this fealure. you must finish a short or long rest before you can use it again.
Insidious Boon					KEY:Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Insidious Boon									CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Profane Soul.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:When you reach 18th level, your pact patron further empowers your wicked spellcraft. When you damage a foe with a warlock spell, add your Wisdom modifier to the damage dealt.

# Order Of The Mutant
Formulas					KEY:Order Of The Mutant ~ Formulas							CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Mutant.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:You begin to uncover forbidden alchemical formulas that temporarily alter your mental and physical abilities. Beginning at 3rd level, you choose to learn three mutagen formulas. Your formula options are detailed at the end of this order description. You gain an additional formula at 7th level, 10th level, 13th level, 15th level, and 20th level. Additionally, when you gain a mutagen formula at levels 7. 10, 13, 15, and 20, you can choose one of the formulas you know and replace it with another mutagen formula.	DEFINE:POOL_WitchHunterMutagen|0	BONUS:VAR|POOL_WitchHunterMutagen|3+(WitchHunterLVL>=7)+(WitchHunterLVL>=10)+(WitchHunterLVL>=13)+(WitchHunterLVL>=15)+(WitchHunterLVL>=20)
Mutagen Craft				KEY:Order Of The Mutant ~ Mutagen Craft						CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Mutant.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 3rd level, you can take a short rest to concoct a single mutagen. Consuming a single mutagen requires a bonus action, and the effects (including side effects) last until you finish another short or long rest. Mutagens are designed for your biology and are fatal to anyone who consumes one other than you. Mutagens are unstable by nature, losing their potency over time and becoming inert if not used before you finish your next short or long rest.
Advanced Mutagen Craft			KEY:Order Of The Mutant ~ Advanced Mutagen Craft				CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Mutant.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Upon reaching 7th level, when you take a short rest to concoct a mutagen, you can now create two. Mutagens must be different formulas, and can be ingested with overlapping effects that last until you finish your next short or long rest. Each mutagen still takes a separate bonus action to imbibe. Once you reach 15th level, you can now create three mutagens during a short rest.
Robust Physiology				KEY:Order Of The Mutant ~ Robust Physiology					CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Mutant.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At l0th level, your body has begun to adapt to toxins and venoms, ignoring their corroding effects. You gain immunity to poison.
Strange Metabolism			KEY:Order Of The Mutant ~ Strange Metabolism					CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Mutant.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Beginning at 15th level, you've become resistant to the negative effects of some your own mutagens. Upon imbibing a mutagen, you can choose to ignore the side effect of that mutagen for its duration. Once you use this feature. you must finish a long rest before you can use it again.
Exalted Fortitude				KEY:Order Of The Mutant ~ Exalted Fortitude					CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Class Feature.ClassAbility.Order Of The Mutant.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:When you reach 18th level, the mutations you've subjected your body to have hardened your physical form. Your Constitution score increases by 2, as does your Constitution maximum.

# Witch Hunter Mutagens
Baleful					KEY:Mutagen ~ Baleful						CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Mutagen.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,7	DESC:Prerequisite: 7th level. You gain resistance to necrotic damage. Side effect: You gain vulnerability to psychic damage.
Celerity					KEY:Mutagen ~ Celerity						CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Mutagen.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.						DESC:Your Dexterity score increases by an amount equal to your Cons \titution modifier (minimum 2), as does your Dexterity maximum. Side effect: Your Wisdom score decreases by 2.
Cruelty					KEY:Mutagen ~ Cruelty						CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Mutagen.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	PREVARGTEQ:WitchHunterLVL,10	DESC:Prerequisite: 10th level. You gain an additional action on each of your turns. That action can be used only to take the Attack (one weapon attack only) action. Side effect: You have disadvantage on all saving throws.
Frigid					KEY:Mutagen ~ Frigid						CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Mutagen.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.						DESC:You gain resistance to cold damage. Side effect: Your speed is reduced by 5.
Impermeable					KEY:Mutagen ~ Impermeable					CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Mutagen.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.						DESC:You gain resistance to piercing damage. Side effect: You gain vulnerability to slashing damage.
Mobility					KEY:Mutagen ~ Mobility						CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Mutagen.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.						DESC:You gain immunity to the grappled and restrained conditions. At 10th level. you also are immune to the paralyzed condition. Side effect: You gain a penalty to initiative equal to 2 times your Constitution modifier (minimum 2).
Nighteye					KEY:Mutagen ~ Nighteye						CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Witch Hunter Mutagen.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.						DESC:You gain darkvisi n for up to 60 feet. If you already have darkvision, this increases its range by 60 additional feet. Side effect: You gain sunlight sensitivity (phb pg. 24)
